<p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder16');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Web Comics&nbsp;</div><div id="folder16" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;">
<ul><li> Played straight in <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/M9Girls" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/M9Girls">M9 Girls!</a></em>: we get a gym training sequence with a page devoted to each Girl showcasing her cosmic power.
</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Subverted" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Subverted">Subverted</a>, parodied and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Invoked" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Invoked">invoked</a> in <a class="urllink" href="http://www.giantitp.com/comics/oots0391.html">this<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/TheOrderOfTheStick" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/TheOrderOfTheStick">Order of the Stick</a></em> strip.
<div class="indent"><strong>Elan:</strong> How come we've only been doing this for twenty minutes, but you've already changed the backdrop five times and gone through three costumes? <br><strong>Julio:</strong> Elan, never underestimate the strategic value of a good Training Scene Montage. It could save your life one day. Though I guess maybe I should actually <em>teach</em> you some of these things...
</div></li><li> <a class="urllink" href="http://drmcninja.com/page.php?pageNum=39&amp;issue=10">This strip<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> of <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/TheAdventuresOfDrMcNinja" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/TheAdventuresOfDrMcNinja">The Adventures of Dr. McNinja</a></em>. Note the image's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AltText" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AltText">Alt Text</a>.
